      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3 for MRL 5 assessment.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022R2) is commercially validated and maintained under ISO 9001 quality management. Version control, regression testing, and release notes are documented. Achieved Gradation 3 confirmed by audit of solver QA records."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy tests performed on canonical rotating-frame flow benchmarks confirm second-order spatial accuracy. Residual convergence criteria tightened to 1e-6 for all equations. Code verification activities documented in internal report MCV-2024-07."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation performed across three systematically refined meshes (2.1M, 6.8M, 18.4M cells). Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index QoI is below 3% on the fine mesh. Temporal discretization error bounded by time-step sensitivity study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Bench test conditions replicate clinical CPB flow range (2–6 L/min) and rotational speed (3000–5000 RPM). Temperature, hematocrit (35%), and fluid viscosity are controlled within ±5% of target. Inlet boundary conditions measured by calibrated ultrasonic flow meters."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison of CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) against bench measurements at 5 operating points. Mean relative error is 8.4%, within the 15% acceptance threshold. Validation metrics computed per ASME V&V 20."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH) derived from the power-law hemolysis damage model. RH directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate). Secondary QoIs include wall shear stress and exposure time distributions, which are the mechanistic drivers of hemolysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments use the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, identical blood analog fluid (glycerin-water mixture calibrated to blood viscosity), and the same operating envelope as the COU. Geometric fidelity between test article and simulation model confirmed by CMM measurement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not established — factor was not assessed.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error was not independently assessed for this submission cycle. Solver error characterization beyond code verification was deferred to a future study. No bounding analysis or sensitivity study was performed to quantify residual solver errors at the operating conditions of the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not established — factor was not assessed.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment was not conducted. No formal review of analyst setup choices, boundary condition application, or post-processing procedures was performed against a documented simulation plan. The potential for user-introduced error in turbulence model selection and hemolysis model parameterization was not characterized."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not established — factor was not assessed.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty arising from the choice of the power-law hemolysis damage model and the SST k-omega turbulence closure was not formally assessed. Alternative model forms were not evaluated and no evidence of model form adequacy relative to the COU physics was documented in this package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (blood density 1060 kg/m³, dynamic viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s), geometric dimensions (within ±0.05 mm CMM tolerance), and operating boundary conditions are documented with uncertainty ranges. Sensitivity of hemolysis index to ±10% perturbations in key inputs evaluated by one-at-a-time analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 2.",
      "rationale": "Three pump units from the same manufacturing lot were used for bench hemolysis testing. Sample-to-sample variability in NIH measurements was within 12%, consistent with expected manufacturing tolerances. Statistical summary of inter-unit variability is reported in test report TR-2024-CBP-03."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level of 3.",
      "rationale": "Equivalency between simulation input parameters and physical test conditions confirmed by direct measurement comparison. Inlet velocity profiles, rotational speed, and fluid properties in the simulation match bench test measurements within documented uncertainty bands. Equivalency table provided in credibility evidence package appendix."
